so its been a while since ive written in here. hm. well, the past month has been an exciting one, i must say. full of more happiness, sadness, excitement, rejection, acceptance, and surprise than i could have thought possible. i am both greatful and resentful for this. its left me in a place ive never been before; a place where im not sure whats what. the only thing i can say that i know for sure anymore is that i have a lot to learn. im having trouble articulating what this feels like, probably because ive never felt it before. now that i think about it, this whole entry is probably making me sound ridiculous, so ill just leave the rest in my head before i confuse you any further.


on a less vague note, i just found out that one of my all time favorite musical artists is actually coming here. =]

so i think this past weekend will be the last time i take part in anything one typically associates with 'partying'. sure, it can be fun. but i miss the kind of fun i had that i didnt end up feeling guilty for. but the only problem with that is that a lot of my friends do those kind of things pretty much on a regular basis. i feel like if i stop, i'll stop being part of our group of friends. i never actually understood the concept of peer pressure until now. its not so much people telling you "hey do this if you want to hang out". its more like a personal feeling. no one is making me do anything, yet i feel like i have to. i hate this feeling and i wish i was strong enough to make the right decision. i just dont want to lose my friends.

i really dont want to move. i know that it wont be moving very far. its actually not far at all. just right down the street. but its not the distance im worried about. i grew up in this house. all of my memories are here. this iisnt just a house, its a home. i know i always talk about how i hate living here in this neighborhood, but the truth is i really dont want to leave. packing everything up is just so depressing. i love this place. i really do. i dont want to go.
